    <item>
      <title>How to play The Curse of Monkey Island on Linux</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/posts/2020-04-14-how-to-play-the-curse-of-monkey-island-on-linux/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 14 Apr 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/posts/2020-04-14-how-to-play-the-curse-of-monkey-island-on-linux/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;As I was always a LucasArts fan in the 90ties, I wanted to use my &amp;ldquo;free time&amp;rdquo; (thanks to the Corona lockdown) for playing this old classics.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I bought Monkey Island 1 + 2 on Steam - with the Proton helper, it starts all easy, out of the box.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Monkey Island 3 and 4 I was buying at Gog (it was cheaper) - no help here to get it running for Linux. (it will still run from Steam out of the box, afaik)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>No HDD space left for ubuntu update, make some space at /boot </title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/posts/2015-05-20-no-hdd-space-left-for-ubuntu-update-make-some-space-at-boot/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 21 May 2015 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/posts/2015-05-20-no-hdd-space-left-for-ubuntu-update-make-some-space-at-boot/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/blog/img/no_hdd_space_left_full.png&#34; alt=&#34;Alt text&#34; title=&#34;your hd is full, make space in /boot&#34;&gt; &lt;br&gt;&#xA;your hd is full, make space in /boot&#xA;aaaa&#xA;make a&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;cd /boot ls -la&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;so you see the &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;/boot&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;`&lt;/span&gt; folder&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/blog/img/no_hdd_space_left_full_lsla.png&#34; alt=&#34;Alt text&#34; title=&#34;screenshot of the boot folder&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;now delete the stuff you don&amp;rsquo;t need anymore:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo aptitude remove linux-image-3.13.0-49-generic&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo apt-get remove ...&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/blog/imgafter_deleting_linux_image.png&#34; alt=&#34;Alt text&#34; title=&#34;ls -la after deleting the linux kernel image&#34;&gt;  &lt;br&gt;&#xA;(ls -la after deleting the linux kernel image)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
